RULE CLASSIFICATION:

S6582 — Optional Chaining (19 issues)
  DESCRIPTION: Prefer optional chaining instead of manual null checks
  MESSAGE: "Prefer using an optional chain expression instead, as it's more concise and easier to read."
  FIX PATTERN: 
    obj && obj.prop  →  obj?.prop
    obj && obj.method()  →  obj?.method()
    a && a.b && a.b.c  →  a?.b?.c
  DIFFICULTY: EASY
  TOP 3 FILES:
    1. scripts/check-sonar-readiness.mjs (3)
    2. src/llm/experience-db.js (2)
    3. src/browser-bridge.js (2)

S6853 — Form Label Association (17 issues)
  DESCRIPTION: A form label must be associated with a control
  MESSAGE: "A form label must be associated with a control."
  FIX PATTERN:
    Option A: <label htmlFor="id"><input id="id" /></label>
    Option B: <label><input /></label>  (nest input inside label)
  DIFFICULTY: EASY
  TOP 3 FILES:
    1. renderer/screens/Accounts.jsx (10) ← 59% of issues here
    2. renderer/screens/BrowserAutomation.jsx (3)
    3. renderer/screens/PromptTemplates.jsx (2)

S7785 — Top-Level Await (13 issues)
  DESCRIPTION: Prefer top-level await over promise chains or async IIFE wrappers
  MESSAGE: "Prefer top-level await over using a promise chain." / "Prefer top-level await over an async function `main` call."
  FIX PATTERN:
    .then(result => { ... }).catch(err => { ... })  →  const result = await ...
    (async () => { await ... })()  →  await ...  (at module level)
  DIFFICULTY: MED (module ESM requirement)
  DISTRIBUTION: Scattered across 13 files (1 each)
    Top: src/cli.js, scripts/check-sonar-readiness.mjs, scripts/reconcile-hotspot-register.mjs

